fields.name: Barra Atlantic
fields.gin_desc: Barra Atlantic Gin showcases a perfect balance of floral and herbal on the nose, leading to juniper, citrus and dulcet carrageen. Refreshing and clean, with a long, gratifyingly warm spice finish.

fields.name: Aviation Gin
fields.gin_desc: The gin takes a Dutch style rye spirit base combined with with juniper, lavender, anise, sarsaparilla, orange peel and cardamom, and the botanicals are steeped in grain spirit.

fields.name: Ballykeefe Extra Dry Irish Gin
fields.gin_desc: Fresh citrus notes with a hint of spice and a lingering floral bouquet. Immediate hit of juniper and citrus, mid palate of warming spiced flavours.Very dry on the finish, making the next sip a must.

fields.name: Birch Gin
fields.gin_desc: A marvellous expression made with the one-shot distillation method and featuring birch syrup as one of its botanicals - which imparts a subtly sweet yet spicy note to the spirit. Alongside the eponymous birch syrup, this expression features the likes of juniper, orange, lime, grapefruit, rosemary, coriander, lemongrass, cardamom, cinnamon, ginger, orris.

fields.name: Bloom Gin
fields.gin_desc: Bloom Gin is a superb London Dry Gin produced by Greenall's and named 'Bloom' in reference to the floral nature of its botanicals: honeysuckle, pomelo and chamomile.

fields.name: Botanist Islay Dry Gin
fields.gin_desc: Barra Atlantic Gin showcases a perfect balance of floral and herbal on the nose, leading to juniper, citrus and dulcet carrageen. Refreshing and clean, with a long, gratifyingly warm spice finish.

fields.name: Curiowild Coast Gin
fields.gin_desc: Delicate and smooth to taste, it's spicy on the palate with balanced botanicals. Perfect to enjoy as a classic G&T or on its own with ice.

fields.name: Daringly Dry London Gin
fields.gin_desc: The carefully created botanical recipe includes juniper berries, coriander, orange and lemon peel, almond and liquorice.

fields.name: East London Dry Gin
fields.gin_desc: East London Liquor Premium Gin Batch 2 is made with botanicals including juniper berries, coriander seeds, angelica root, thyme, winter savory, fennel seed, orris root, lavender, lemon peel, sage and bay leaf.

fields.name: Eden Mill Original Gin
fields.gin_desc: Barra Atlantic Gin showcases a perfect balance of floral and herbal on the nose, leading to juniper, citrus and dulcet carrageen. Refreshing and clean, with a long, gratifyingly warm spice finish

fields.name: Edinburgh Gin
fields.gin_desc: Beautifully balanced and crafted with warm spiciness, tangy sweetness, more juniper and more gin. Our Classic London Dry is at the base.

fields.name: Bombay Sapphire
fields.gin_desc: Light and piney juniper, with soft peppery warmth building. Subtle sweetness of sugared almond and angelica develops, still packed with herbaceousness.

fields.name: In Flames
fields.gin_desc: The lingonberries were macerated together with the cranberries over a few warm summer days before they were distilled and added to the gin.

fields.name: Gordon Castle Gin
fields.gin_desc: Gordon Castle Gin is a crisp, elegant and refreshing gin with a lovely clean palate. Subtle notes of lavender linger in the back of the nose and within the mouth. Garden mint comes into focus helping promote the clean and refreshing character.

fields.name: Drumshanbo Gunpowder Gin
fields.gin_desc: Here at the edge of a lake in a shed in a small Irish town, the ordinary is made extraordinary. Within is the laboratory of Rigney, boundary-pushing begetter of hand- made spirits who slow distills gin with natures finest oriental botanicals and gunpowder tea.

fields.name: Hendricks Gin
fields.gin_desc: From its floral aroma of violet and rose to the subtle hint of spice, Hendrick's Gin takes the senses on a wonderful adventure. Botanicals are sourced from exotic flowers, fruits and seeds all over the world, making it crisp, zesty and entirely exquisite.

fields.name: Kings Hill Gin
fields.gin_desc: Piney Juniper berries form the perfect backbone of our gin. Locally-foraged Heather, Rosehips, Gorse and Elderflower.

fields.name: Land of Saints Organic Gin
fields.gin_desc: Land of Saints is produced with 13 organic botanicals, which make for an exceptionally smooth, fresh, citrus led gin with floral notes and a well balanced level of juniper.

fields.name: L&C Gin
fields.gin_desc: A beautiful balanced gin that has plenty of classic pine notes from juniper and then the layers of lime and cardamom really come through.

fields.name: Masham Classic Gold
fields.gin_desc: Goldings Hops and Golden Berries interwoven with Lime Peel and Orange Peel. Kaffir Lime Leaves, Lemon Grass and Pomelo peel. A little kick of black and pink peppercorn too.

fields.name: Old Curiosity Lemon Verbena Gin
fields.gin_desc: Natural citrus notes, a hint of lemon sherbet, this is a refreshing dry gin with a slight salinity to the finish.

fields.name: Orkney Gin Johnsmas
fields.gin_desc: Johnsmas is a highly floral, fragrant and light gin made with a selection of hand-picked botanicals from the island of Orkney.

fields.name: Shetland Reel Gin
fields.gin_desc: Made with a specially devised recipe featuring 8 botanicals, including juniper, coriander seed, orris root, cassia bark, citrus peel and apple mint.

fields.name: Pickerings Gin
fields.gin_desc: Finely-tuned, the ingredients featuring botanicals like Juniper, Lemon, Lime, Coriander, Anise, Angelica, Cardamom, Clove and Fennel shine through.

fields.name: Roku Japanese Gin
fields.gin_desc: Infused with a selection of plants, representing the four seasons: sakura leaves, and sakura blossom for spring, sencha tea and gyokuro tea for summer, pepper sansho for autumn and yuzu peel for winter.

fields.name: Salcombe Gin 'Start Point'
fields.gin_desc: Distilled with 13 fine botanicals hand sourced from around the world, including Macedonian juniper, English coriander seed and fresh citrus.

fields.name: Siblings Lemon & Rosemary Gin
fields.gin_desc: Infused with fresh lemon zest and rosemary. This is the perfect gin for a spring G&T, served with a slice of lemon and lots of ice.

fields.name: Sipsmith London Dry Gin
fields.gin_desc: Floral, summer meadow notes, followed by mellow rounded juniper and zesty, citrus freshness. Dry juniper leads, then reveals lemon tart & orange marmalade.

fields.name: Herno Swedish Gin
fields.gin_desc: Smell of pine trees bursts out of the bottle. A sweet juniper and spicy coriander balance out the mix, with slightly muted vanilla.

fields.name: Kyrö Gin
fields.gin_desc: The palate adds more floral and perfumed qualities, Parma Violets and a touch of rich heather, among bolder kicks of spice, which include a little cinnamon.

fields.name: Glacier Icelandic Gin
fields.gin_desc: Glacier Gin is made from selected high quality ingredients to ensure a fresh and good taste. Mix double Glacier Gin and tonic with lots of cloves and a slice of lemon peel.

fields.name: Alkkemist Gin
fields.gin_desc: Triple-distilled grain spirit and 21 different botanicals, interestingly including Muscat grape, alongside orange and lemon peel, rose petals, samphire, fennel, thyme and mint, among others.

fields.name: Ungava Gin
fields.gin_desc: Named after the Ungava Peninsula which is in Quebec, Canada. Sweet Berries run throughout this alongside a finish of Peppermint and a hint of Caramel.

fields.name: Glengowrie Thunderbolt Gin
fields.gin_desc: Handcrafted with robust botanicals, and showcases the endangered New England peppermint gum. Flavours are citrus and gentle warm pepper.

fields.name: Thomson Victor Gin
fields.gin_desc: Heavy botanical style gin hand-crafted in New Zealand. Juniper, lemon, lemongrass, cardamom and coriander.

fields.name: Malfy Gin Rosa
fields.gin_desc: This ace Italian gin is built around the awesomeness of Sicilian pink grapefruit, and features a hint of rhubarb too.

fields.name: Canaima
fields.gin_desc: Straight from the Amazon rainforest. 10 indigenous botanicals makes for a grassy,refreshing and herbaceous spirit. There’s a peppery kick and a general earthiness, as well as a lingering, fruity sweetness.

fields.name: Broken Bones Gin
fields.gin_desc: This London dry gin is distilled with juniper and other botanicals from Slovenia’s Karst region to create an appealing medley of floral, citrus and spice notes.
